com.foreach.across.modules.dynamicforms.domain.document.data.expressions

Class BuildDynamicDocumentFormulaEvaluationContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.dynamicforms.domain.document.data.expressions.BuildDynamicDocumentFormulaEvaluationContext

  • public final class BuildDynamicDocumentFormulaEvaluationContext
extends Object
    Event published when the EvaluationContext for a specific document should be created. During execution a property document will added to access the fields of the document.

    When this event is published the default evaluation context will be set. The default evaluation context does not allow bean resolving but registers the formula helper functions.

    Note that when manually specifying the evaluation context to use, no EvaluationContext.getRootObject() should be set as that will always be the DynamicDocumentFieldFormulaContext of the field being evaluated.

    Since:
    0.0.2
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
